sql:
SELECT customer_id, engagement_score
FROM customer_engagement
WHERE engagement_score > 70;

external_knowledge:
- Average engagement score represents the overall interaction of a customer group with the bank.; 
- Tenure refers to the length of time a customer has been with the bank.; 
- Exited customers are those who have stopped banking with the institution.; 
- Customers allowing data sharing are those who have opted-in to share their banking data.
